    {
      "type": "Requested Content",
      "text": "Type of financial institution (column 1) \nSelect the option which most closely describes your organization.\nOrganization type (column 2) \nSelect the option which most closely matches your organization type. See the \"Explanation of terms\" for details of the different types. \nIf you are a parent organization responding on behalf of subsidiaries, select the option which reflects your status as the parent organization. \nDescription of organization (column 3) \nIf disclosing climate change data, specify your business divisions and emissions sources (e.g., natural resource extraction and/or processing, electricity generation, transportation, manufacturing) to help data users understand your emissions profile and compare it with peers. \nSupply Chain program responders only : Include details to provide transparency on which subsidiaries you are including in your response. \nDescription of legislative mandate (column 4) \nThis column only appears to disclosers identified as a public authority. \nDescribe your organization's legislative mandate to help data users understand your governance responses, degree of autonomy and influence.",
      "typeKo": "요청 내용",
      "textKo": "Type of financial institution (열 1) Select the option which most closely 설명s 귀사. Organization type (열 2) Select the option which most closely matches 귀사 type. See the \"설명 of terms\" for details 의 different types. 만약 you are a parent organization responding on behalf of subsidiaries, select the option which reflects your status as the parent organization. Description of organization (열 3) 만약 disclosing climate change data, specify your business divisions 및 emissions sources (e.g., natural resource extraction 및/또는 프로세스ing, electricity generation, transportation, manufacturing) to help 데이터 사용자 understand your emissions profile 및 compare it with peers. 공급망 program responders only: Include details to provide transparency on which subsidiaries you are 포함 in your response. Description of legislative mandate (열 4) This 열 only appears to disclosers identified as a 공개 authority. 설명 귀사의 legislative mandate to help 데이터 사용자 understand your 거버넌스 responses, degree of autonomy 및 influence."
    },
    {
      "type": "Explanation of Terms",
      "text": "Environmental issues: this refers to your organization's dependencies, impacts, risks, and opportunities related to the environmental issue areas covered in CDP's corporate questionnaire i.e., climate change, water, forests, ocean, biodiversity and/or plastics. \nLegislative mandate: a legal directive or authority granted by legislation, specifying an organization's purpose including, but not limited to, powers, responsibilities, obligations and accountability. \nOrganization: throughout this questionnaire, \"your organization\" and \"organization-wide\" refer collectively to all the companies, businesses, other groups etc. that fall within the definition of your reporting boundary (provided in 1.5). This term is used interchangeably with \"your company\", but CDP recognizes that some disclosing organizations may not consider themselves to be, or be formally classified, as \"companies\". \nPrivately owned organization : an organization whose ownership is typically held by a small group of individuals, or a single entity and its shares are not traded on a public stock exchange. \nPublicly traded organization : an organization whose ownership is distributed among public shareholders through publicly traded stock shares. \nState owned organization : an organization formed by governments in order to take part in commercial activities.",
      "typeKo": "설명 of Terms",
      "textKo": "환경 이슈: this refers to 귀사의 dependencies, impacts, 리스크, 및 기회 related to the environmental issue areas covered in CDP's corporate 질문서 i.e., climate change, water, forests, ocean, biodiversity 및/또는 plastics. Legislative mandate: a legal directive 또는 authority granted by legislation, specifying an 조직의 purpose 포함, but not limited to, powers, responsibilities, obligations 및 accountability. Organization: throughout this 질문서, \"귀사\" 및 \"organization-wide\" refer collectively to all the companies, businesses, other groups etc. that fall within the definition of your 보고경계 (입력 in 1.5). This term is used interchangeably with \"your company\", but CDP recognizes that some disclosing organizations may not consider themselves to be, 또는 be formally classified, as \"companies\". Privately owned organization: an organization whose ownership is typically held by a small group of individuals, 또는 a single entity 및 its shares are not traded on a 공개 stock exchange. 공개ly traded organization: an organization whose ownership is distributed among 공개 shareholders through 공개ly traded stock shares. owned organization을/를 입력하십시오.: an organization formed by governments in order to take part in commercial activities."
    }
  ],
